    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini. Imperante domno nostro <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/110">Hlodohuvicus</persName> magnus <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >imperator</rs>, anno quinto decimo, die de mense novembris, indictione
                        terdia decima, feliciter. Breve recordationis qualiter <persName
                            ref="#people/340" key="#Missus_regis #Bishops">Vualpertus</persName>
                        Motinense ecclesie <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Missus_regis">missus</rs> domni imperatoris veniens <placeName
                            ref="#places/33"
                            key="#Houses #Rivers #Curtes #Forests #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Exceptive #Dowry #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Churches #Royal_slave"
                                ><geogName ref="#estates/40"
                                key="#Houses #Rivers #Curtes #Cereals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Exceptive #Dowry #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Churches #Royal_slave"
                                >Vuardestalla</geogName></placeName>, habens exsemplar <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepti</rs> domni imperatoris quem ab
                        multimode dilectionis <rs key="#Queen">auguste</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/55" key="#Queen">Inghelberge</persName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Exceptive #Dowry #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals"
                            >iure proprietario</rs> domno imperator predicta <rs key="#Curtes"
                            >curtem</rs> cum <rs key="#Churches">capella</rs> et dote sua, cum
                        omnibus <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis et ancillis</rs> ac <rs key="#Houses"
                            >domibus</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">agris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis, pascuis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumque
                            decursibus</rs> cunctisque in integrum ab eandem curtem aspicientibus
                        seu omnibus movilibus et inmovilibus iuxte e legaliter ab eandem
                        pertinentibus perpetualiter habendum concesserat. Quod exemplare lectum
                        eorum presentia quorum nomina subto leguntur, idest <persName
                            key="#Chaplain #Consiliarius_regis"><name ref="Tancredus"
                                >Tancheradus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chaplain">capellanus</rs> et <rs key="#Consiliarius_regis"
                            >consiliarius</rs> domni imperatoris, <persName><name ref="Gisbertus"
                                >Gisebertus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Adulfus"
                                >Adulfus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Deusdedit"
                                >Deusdedit</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ragifredus"
                                >Ragimfredus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ragibertus"
                                >Ragimbertus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Adelbertus"
                                >Adelbertus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Teudericus"
                                >Teudericus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petro</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Atrepaldus"
                                >Atrepaldo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Natio"><name
                                ref="Amicus">Amicho</name></persName> ex <rs key="#Natio">genere
                            Francorum</rs>, <persName key="#Natio"><name ref="Teupertus"
                                >Teusperto</name></persName> ex genere Francorum, <persName
                            key="#Alemannus"><name ref="Fulcherius">Fulcherius</name></persName> ex
                            <rs key="#Alemannus">genere Alammanorum</rs>, <persName key="#Priests"
                                ><name ref="Iohannacis">Ioanace</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs>, <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Vitalis">Vitale</name></persName> presbiter, <persName><name
                                ref="Austreuertus">Austreverto</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Priests #Natio"><name ref="Germanus">Germano</name></persName>
                        presbiter ex genere Francorum, <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Robertus"
                                >Roperto</name></persName> presbiter, <persName><name
                                ref="Adelbaldus">Hadebald</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diacono</rs> ex genere Francorum, <persName
                            key="#Deacons"><name ref="Ildebertus">Ildeberto</name></persName>
                        diacono, <persName key="#Deacons"><name ref="Robertus"
                            >Roperto</name></persName> diacono, <persName key="#Lombard"><name
                                ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Lombard">Langobardo</rs>, <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Ursus">Urso</name></persName> presbiter, <persName key="#Natio"
                                ><name ref="Luvegisus">Luvegiso</name></persName> ex genere
                        Francorum, <persName key="#Natio"><name ref="Adrebertus"
                            >Adreverto</name></persName> ex genere Francorum, <persName
                            key="#Notary"><name ref="Grimbertus">Grinebertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>, <persName key="#Alemannus"><name
                                ref="Inglericus">Inglericus</name></persName> ex genere Alamannorum.
                        In istorum omnium superscriptorum praesentia, post relectum exemplar,
                        iamdictus Vualpertus episcopus ex iussione domni imperatoris a parte domne
                        Ingheberghae auguste <persName key="#Other_minor_officer"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petrum</name></persName> iuris eius <rs key="#Other_minor_officer"
                            >famulum et ministrum</rs> vicem eiusdem augustem per columnam de domo
                        eiusdem curtis iamfatum Petrum revestivit iure proprietario sicut in eandem
                        contenebatur exemplar. Actum est haec in predicta curtem Vuardestalla, die
                        IIII kalendas december, feliciter. + Ego Vualpertus episcopus et misso domni
                        imperatoris pos acta tradizione suscripsi. (C) Ego Tandiradus supranominatus
                        interfui. Ego Urso presbiter supranominatus interfui. (C) Ego Iohennatius
                        presbiter supranominatus interfui. Ego Roperto presbiter supernominatus
                        interfuit. Ego Ildepertus diaconus supranominatus interfuit. (C) Ego
                        Germanus presbiter supranominatus interfui. Signum Anteberti interfuit. (C)
                        Ego Grinbertus notarius supranominatus interfui. + Ego Giseverto interfui. +
                        Ego Ragimfrido interfui. + Signum Inglerixi qui interfuit. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
